OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FAttack victims hit out at  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fextremism in open letter   
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, More than 50 victims of                
OL,6, Islamist-inspired terror attacks have  
OL,7, signed a joint letter against what they
OL,8, describe as anti-Muslim hate.          
OL,10,FThey warn it is "irresponsible" for    
OL,11,Fsome politicians to equate extremists  
OL,12,Fwith "the vast majority of British     
OL,13,FMuslims who deplore such violence".    
OL,15,FSurvivors and relatives of those killed
OL,16,Fduring attacks in London, Manchester   
OL,17,Fand Brussels are among the signatories.
OL,19,FIt comes as the government prepares to 
OL,20,Fset out a new definition of extremism. 
